                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14470725" author="blackdrag" created="Wed, 5 Jan 2011 02:28:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it is a bug and there should be a check for the modifier&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14470854" author="guillaume" created="Thu, 3 Feb 2011 15:33:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added a check to disallow static for outer classes, as this has no meaning.&lt;br/&gt;
However, I&apos;ve committed the fix only in 1.8, as it may be a breaking change (ie. code possibly not compiling anymore) if users used that modifier on some of their classes. Fortunately, the presence or absence of this modifier in that context has no impact whatsoever (it&apos;s just that it&apos;s useless to use it, but the compiler doesn&apos;t treat that in any way).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
